{"title":"Campagnolo’s Ekar GT 1×13 Groupset Sports a Wider Range Cassette","link":"https://theradavist.com/campagnolos-ekar-gt-1x13-groupset/","date":1708442338000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2724\" height=\"1816\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/RUD8253.jpg?fit=1200,1816&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/RUD8253.jpg?w=2724&amp;quality=75 2724w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/RUD8253.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/RUD8253.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/RUD8253.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/RUD8253.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/RUD8253.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>Campagnolo’s Ekar 1×13 groupset intrigued us when John <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/cotic-escapade-853-review/\" target=\"_blank\">first rode it in his Cotic Escapade review</a>. It’s a crisp-shifting, wide range gravel group that shifts like the almighty Campy 8-speed drivetrains. Announced today is the <a href=\"https://www.campagnolo.com/us-en/livestory-pages/new-ekar-gt-groupset-and-zonda-gt-wheelset/gt-collection.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ekar GT 1×13 Groupset</a> with a new 10-48 cassette and revised hood ergonomics and new <a href=\"https://www.campagnolo.com/us-en/livestory-pages/new-ekar-gt-groupset-and-zonda-gt-wheelset/gt-collection.html\" target=\"_blank\">Zonda GT Wheels</a>. Let’s check it all out below…<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/Campagnolo-EKARgt-2024.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/Campagnolo-EKARgt-2024.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/Campagnolo-EKARgt-2024.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/Campagnolo-EKARgt-2024.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/Campagnolo-EKARgt-2024.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Ekar GT Quick Hits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>All Aluminum crankset: 170, 172.5, 175 Lengths, with 151mm Q-Factor<br />\n​- 104mm BCD, 44, 42, 40, 38, and 36 Chainring options</li>\n<li>Cassette Options: 9-36*, 9-42, 10-44, 10-48</li>\n<li>New Improved Hood Ergonomics</li>\n<li>Groupset Weight: 2,700g</li>\n<li>Groupset MSRP: $1,599</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Ekar GT is designed to be incredibly versatile, offering a wide-range 1×13 drivetrain with the combination of four cassette options (9-36, 9-42, 10-44,10-48) and five chainrings (44, 42, 40, 38, and the new 36). This extensive range of options enables every cyclist to select the gear ratio that suits their specific adventure and is Campagnolo’s widest gear range.</p>\n<p>The new Ekar GT crankset features a much easier chainring swapping method, allowing for quick and easy swaps without the painstaking dismantling of its predecessor.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2880\" height=\"2880\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?fit=1200,2880&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?w=2880&amp;quality=75 2880w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?resize=1200,1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?resize=2000,2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/ZondaGT_Completel_V1.png?resize=2048,2048&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2660\" height=\"1774\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/DSC_4263.jpg?fit=1200,1774&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/DSC_4263.jpg?w=2660&amp;quality=75 2660w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/DSC_4263.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/DSC_4263.jpg?resize=2000,1334&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/DSC_4263.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/DSC_4263.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/02/DSC_4263.jpg?resize=2048,1366&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Zonda GT Quick Hits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Weight: 1690gr</li>\n<li>23mm internal rim width</li>\n<li>29mm deep rim profile</li>\n<li>Available with N3W, HG, and XDR Freehub Bodies</li>\n<li>Cup and Cone Bearing Internals</li>\n<li>MSRP: $749</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Zonda GT harkens back to Campagnolo’s roots as developing ultralight, fast spinning wheels, with a unique 8×3 G3 lacing geometry and cup and cone bearings.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>See the full launch at <a href=\"https://www.campagnolo.com/us-en/livestory-pages/new-ekar-gt-groupset-and-zonda-gt-wheelset/gt-collection.html\" target=\"_blank\">Campagnolo</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/campagnolos-ekar-gt-1x13-groupset/\">Campagnolo’s Ekar GT 1×13 Groupset Sports a Wider Range Cassette</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"0ddb11559d312990faf551f7ecfb5f7b064c6ae4ebcc8d2b8ec998a633cdf37f","category":"Cycling"}